      "message": "PTAL at the new patch.\n\nSome findings in the integration test:\n1. swarming rejects the request because \"ResultDB is enabled, but realm is not set\". And that\u0027s because currently swarming tasks don\u0027t have realms with them: https://screenshot.googleplex.com/244bab86-8cba-454a-bb16-eefe1c4f3acc\n2. So I used \"chromium:public\" realm to make the request, and I got a 403: user \"chanli@google.com\" does not have permission \"swarming.tasks.createInRealm\"\n\nBecause of above findings, I think this change may be blocked on swarming tasks having realms. \n\nI also thought about hardcode the realm to \"chromium:public\" for chromium ci/try jobs and fix the permission, but I\u0027m not sure if it\u0027s necessary or how much value could it add.",
